  "prompt": "What is the best dictionary app for iphone?",
  "response": "There are several excellent dictionary apps for iPhone, each with its own unique features. Here are some of the best options:\n\n1. **Merriam-Webster Dictionary**: This app offers a comprehensive dictionary, thesaurus, word games, and audio pronunciations. It's user-friendly and highly regarded for its extensive word database.\n\n2. **Oxford English Dictionary**: Known for its authoritative content, this app provides detailed definitions, etymology, and usage examples. It offers a subscription model for access to advanced features.\n\n3. **Dictionary.com**: This app includes a vast dictionary and thesaurus, along with features like word of the day, quizzes, and offline access, making it very versatile for users.\n\n4. **Collins English Dictionary**: Collins offers not just definitions but also translations and language resources. The app is well-designed and includes a special feature for learning new vocabulary.\n\n5. **WordWeb Dictionary**: This app provides definitions, synonyms, and antonyms, along with a built-in thesaurus. It works offline, which is a significant plus.\n\n6. **Vocabulary.com**: While more of a tool for learning and reinforcing vocabulary, it also serves as a great dictionary. It provides example sentences and quizzes based on the user's personal vocabulary challenges.\n\n7. **Cambridge Dictionary**: Focuses on clear, easy-to-understand definitions, with a focus on contemporary English. It also offers example sentences and audio pronunciations.\n\nDepending on your needs\u2014whether you want a comprehensive dictionary, language learning features, or offline access\u2014any of these apps could be considered the best for you.",
